d zukünftig stellen muss. Aus verschiedenen Blickwinkeln analysieren die Autor*innen Angebot und Nachfrage von Flusskreuzfahrten in Deutschland, Trends in der Produktentwicklung, Auswirkungen des demografischen Wandels oder aktuelle Herausforderungen wie die der Nachhaltigkeit. Zahlreiche Abbildungen und Beispiele unterstreichen die Bedeutung und das große Potenzial dieses touristischen Segments für den Markt.  aThe market for river cruises in Germany grew by 8 percent in 2017. River cruises, however, comprise only a small proportion of the overall cruise market. The authors of this volume take various perspectives to analyze the supply and demand for river cruises in Germany, trends in product development, the impact of demographic change, and current challenges.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 4aCSR. 4aCovid-19-Pandemie. 4aFlusskreuzfahrt. 4aKreuzfahrt. 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aProduktmodifikationen. 4aTourismus. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  aRiver cruises.  acruises.  acustomer journey.  atourism.1 aCarstensen, Ines, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFabisch, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmes, Kirsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIna,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJäger, Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMenke, Kai Ingo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPforr, Christof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider, Stan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShanka, Tekl